pageContext.claim: “We've rejected this failed approach, and we're seeing incredible results. Since the election, we have created more than 6 million new jobs.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump often inflates the number of jobs created under his presidency by counting from Election Day, rather than when he took the oath of office. At the time of this statement, there had been about 5.3 million jobs created since January 2017, according to the Bureau of Labor Statistics. Job growth under Trump in the first two years was little different than Obama's last two years.
